# No Demo Files Policy

## Context
- When implementing new features or APIs
- When adding new functionality to existing systems
- When updating interfaces or libraries

## Requirements
- NEVER create demo files, example scripts, or sample implementations
- Directly integrate new functionality into existing code
- Focus on production implementation only
- Update actual usage points in the codebase

## Examples
<example>
User asks to add grammar constraints to LLM inference.
Response: Update the actual inference calls in commentary_action.py to use the new grammar features.
</example>

<example type="invalid">
